FRONTLINE ROADS v0.31.1 OFFLINE SIMULATION EQUIVALENCE AUDIT

Release: 0.31.1-offline-equivalence
Save key: unchanged
Schema version: unchanged

Implemented:
- Offline progression uses a canonical maximum step of 0.25 seconds instead of adaptive 1.2–5 second coarse updates.
- Offline iteration capacity increased to cover the complete 12-hour cap without truncation.
- Defense reloads preserve elapsed-time overrun and execute every action that became due.
- Facility disable timers pass the remaining operational time into the same update.
- Enemy and friendly departure delays preserve unused update time.
- Enemy and friendly movement carries distance across multiple road edges.
- Enemy slow expiration is split at the exact expiry boundary.
- Barrier attacks preserve the 0.5-second cadence and continue after destruction when update time remains.
- Enemy-base reconciliation preserves its 30-second clock remainder.
- Regional combat substeps are capped at 0.25 seconds.

Equivalence evidence:
- Tower reload: live 0.05-second updates and one coarse elapsed interval produce the same HP and cooldown.
- Enemy departure and multi-edge traversal: live and coarse updates produce the same node, edge and progress.
- Deterministic 60-second CombatSystem interval: live 20 Hz and offline 4 Hz state are identical.
- Long-duration checkpoints at 30 minutes, 1 hour, 4 hours and 12 hours: enemy HP, tower cooldown, kills, city HP and world time are identical.
- 12-hour stationary-defense benchmark: 115,200 offline iterations, approximately 1.7 seconds in this container.
- Existing connected-road 12-hour simulation completes within the iteration, enemy-count and save-size limits.

